ter in the mass-size relation may\nhave previously been overestimated by ~25%. Moreover, orientation-driven\nscatter causes the number density of very massive galaxies to be overestimated\nby ~0.5 dex at $M_*\\sim10^{11.5}M_{\\odot}$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Jul 2017 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 26 Jul 2017 05:04:25 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-27"}
