\nThese two assertions generalize the classical Schwartz reflection principle for\nharmonic functions and holomorphic functions on the complex plane to harmonic\nmaps and holomorphic maps from a class of Hermitian symmetric spaces admitting\nrecursive real forms. A reflection principle for meromorphic functions defined\non the complex plane and taking on real values on the real line is also proved.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 4 Jul 2017 18:05:42 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 19 Jul 2017 17:12:50 GMT"}],"update_date":"2017-07-20"}
